[32m+[m[32m# UNDERSTANDING THE TERMS (SIMPLE EXPLANATION)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## What is DR (Disaster Recovery)?[m
[32m+[m[32m**Answer for the jury:** "Disaster Recovery is our plan for when something goes wrong - like the server crashing, a natural disaster, or a cyber attack. It answers: How do we get back online? How long will it take? How much data might we lose?"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## What is DC (Data Recovery)?[m
[32m+[m[32m**Answer for the jury:** "Data Recovery is about protecting our data. It's the backup strategy - ensuring that if we lose data, we can recover it. We back up the database, the ML models, and the embeddings so nothing is permanently lost."[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## What is BCP (Business Continuity Planning)?[m
[32m+[m[32m**Answer for the jury:** "Business Continuity is about keeping the business running EVEN when systems fail. It's not just about recovery - it's about having fallbacks so customers never experience service interruption. In our case, if the LLM API is down, we still process complaints using rule-based fallbacks."[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# WHY THESE MATTER FOR COMPLAINTIQ[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## The Banking Context[m
[32m+[m[32mBanks are critical infrastructure. RBI expects:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Business continuity plans[m
[32m+[m[32m- Data backup strategies[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- Recovery procedures[m
[32m+[m[32m- Minimal downtime[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mFor a complaint management system, the stakes are high:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Customer data must be protected[m
[32m+[m[32m- SLA tracking must continue even during issues[m
[32m+[m[32m- Regulatory compliance must be maintained[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# PART 1: DISASTER RECOVERY (DR) PLAN[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 1.1 What Could Go Wrong?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Scenario | Impact | Our Protection |[m
[32m+[m[32m|----------|--------|----------------|[m
[32m+[m[32m| Server crash | App goes down | Fallback servers, restart procedures |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Database corruption | Data loss | Regular backups, recovery procedures |[m
[32m+[m[32m| ML model file corrupt | Predictions fail | Backup models, fallback to rules |[m
[32m+[m[32m| ChromaDB corruption | Duplicate detection fails | Rebuild index capability |[m
[32m+[m[32m| LLM API down | Classification stops | Rule-based fallbacks |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 1.2 Key Metrics We Need to Define[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### RTO (Recovery Time Objective)[m
[32m+[m[32m**Question:** How long can we be down?[m
[32m+[m[32m**Our Target:** 30 minutes for full recovery[m
[32m+[m[32m**Why:** Banking complaints are time-sensitive, but 30 min is realistic for manual intervention[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### RPO (Recovery Point Objective)[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m**Question:** How much data can we afford to lose?[m
[32m+[m[32m**Our Target:** Maximum 1 hour of data[m
[32m+[m[32m**Why:** Complaints come in continuously, but hourly backups are manageable[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 1.3 Recovery Procedures[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Scenario A: Complete Server Failure[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mIMMEDIATE ACTIONS:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Identify backup server (can be local machine, cloud instance)[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Deploy latest backup of:[m
[32m+[m[32m   - SQLite database (data/complaintiq.sqlite)[m
[32m+[m[32m   - ML models (models/*.joblib)[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m   - ChromaDB (data/chroma_db/)[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Configuration files[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Restart application[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Verify functionality[m
[32m+[m[32m5. Resume operations[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Scenario B: Database Corruption[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mIMMEDIATE ACTIONS:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Stop application to prevent further corruption[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Identify last good backup (by timestamp)[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Restore from backup[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Identify any data created between backup and crash[m
[32m+[m[32m5. If possible, replay/re-enter that data (from source systems)[m
[32m+[m[32m6. Verify database integrity[m
[32m+[m[32m7. Resume operations[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Scenario C: ML Model Failure[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mIMMEDIATE ACTIONS:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Detect model load failure (code handles this gracefully)[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Fall back to rule-based predictions:[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Category: Keyword matching[m
[32m+[m[32m   - SLA: Formula-based probability[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Priority: Simple weighted formula[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Log warning for monitoring[m
[32m+[m[32m4. System continues operating (degraded, but functional)[m
[32m+[m[32m5. Replace model file when fixed[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
