[32m+[m[32m## 2.2 Model 2: Category Classifier (TF-IDF + Logistic Regression)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2.2.1 Problem Statement[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Question to Answer:** Which category does this complaint belong to?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Categories:**[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **UPI** - Unified Payments Interface issues[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **ATM** - ATM cash withdrawal issues[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **Card** - Credit/debit card issues[m
[32m+[m[32m4. **Loan** - Loan-related complaints[m
[32m+[m[32m5. **NetBanking** - Online banking issues[m
[32m+[m[32m6. **General** - Everything else[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Why This Matters:**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Different categories = different SLA windows[m
[32m+[m[32m- Different teams handle different categories[m
[32m+[m[32m- Need accurate routing to the right team[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2.2.2 Algorithm: TF-IDF Explained[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### What is TF-IDF?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**TF-IDF = Term Frequency × Inverse Document Frequency**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIt's a way to convert text into numbers (features) while giving importance to meaningful words.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Step 1: Term Frequency (TF)**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHow often does a word appear in a document?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mTF(word, document) = count of word in document[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Step 2: Inverse Document Frequency (IDF)**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHow rare is this word across all documents?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mIDF(word) = log(total_documents / documents_containing_word)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mExample:[m
[32m+[m[32m- "UPI" appears in 50 out of 1000 documents[m
[32m+[m[32m- IDF(UPI) = log(1000/50) = log(20) ≈ 3.0 (rare = important!)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- "the" appears in 1000 out of 1000 documents[m
[32m+[m[32m- IDF(the) = log(1000/1000) = log(1) = 0 (common = not important!)[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Step 3: TF-IDF Weight**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mTF-IDF(word, document) = TF(word, document) × IDF(word)[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Example:**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mDocument: "UPI payment failed, money debited but not credited"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Word | TF | IDF | TF-IDF |[m
[32m+[m[32m|------|-----|-----|--------|[m
[32m+[m[32m| UPI | 1 | 3.0 | 3.0 |[m
[32m+[m[32m| payment | 1 | 1.5 | 1.5 |[m
[32m+[m[32m| failed | 1 | 2.0 | 2.0 |[m
[32m+[m[32m| money | 1 | 0.5 | 0.5 |[m
[32m+[m[32m| the | 2 | 0 | 0 |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m"UPI" gets HIGH weight (rare but important)[m
[32m+[m[32m"the" gets ZERO weight (too common)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2.2.3 Algorithm: Logistic Regression Explained[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**What is Logistic Regression?**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mDespite the name, it's a classifier (not regression). It predicts which class something belongs to.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**The Core Idea:**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mFor each category, we learn a WEIGHT for each word. Then we calculate a score for each category and convert to probability.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Mathematical Formulation:**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mFor a document with TF-IDF vector x, probability of category c:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mP(category=c | x) = exp(w_c · x) / Σⱼ exp(w_j · x)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhere:[m
[32m+[m[32m- w_c = weight vector for category c[m
[32m+[m[32m- w_j = weight vector for category j[m
[32m+[m[32m- x = TF-IDF vector of the document[m
[32m+[m[32m- · = dot product (sum of element-wise multiplication)[m
[32m+[m[32m- exp = e^x (exponential function)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Σ = sum over all categories[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis is called **softmax** - it converts scores to probabilities that sum to 1.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Binary Case (One-vs-Rest):**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mFor 6 categories, we train 6 binary classifiers:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Classifier 1: Is this UPI? (Yes/No)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Classifier 2: Is this ATM? (Yes/No)[m
[32m+[m[32m- ... etc.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2.2.4 Feature Engineering for Text[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Text Preprocessing:**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32m# Original complaint text:[m
[32m+[m[32m# "UPI payment of Rs.5000 failed, money debited but not credited"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Step 1: Lowercase[m
[32m+[m[32m# "upi payment of rs.5000 failed, money debited but not credited"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Step 2: Remove special characters (handled by TF-IDF strip_accents)[m
[32m+[m[32m# "upi payment of rs5000 failed money debited but not credited"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Step 3: TF-IDF vectorization[m
[32m+[m[32m# Creates a sparse vector of ~10,000 features[m
[32m+[m[32m# Most are 0, few are non-zero (the important words)[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**N-grams (capturing phrases):**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWe use (1, 2) n-grams - single words AND pairs:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32m"credit card" → treated as one feature[m
[32m+[m[32m"debit card"  → treated as one feature[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m"net banking" → treated as one feature[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2.2.5 Model Training Process[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Step 1: Text Vectorization**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32m# TF-IDF Vectorizer with parameters[m
[32m+[m[32mvectorizer = TfidfVectorizer([m
[32m+[m[32m    ngram_range=(1, 2),      # Unigrams + bigrams[m
[32m+[m[32m    min_df=2,                # Ignore terms appearing in <2 docs[m
[32m+[m[32m    max_features=10000,     # Max 10k features[m
[32m+[m[32m    sublinear_tf=True,       # Use 1 + log(TF) instead of raw TF[m
[32m+[m[32m    strip_accents="unicode"  # Handle accented characters[m
[32m+[m[32m)[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Step 2: Logistic Regression**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32m# Logistic Regression with parameters[m
[32m+[m[32mclassifier = LogisticRegression([m
[32m+[m[32m    max_iter=2000,           # Max iterations for convergence[m
[32m+[m[32m    class_weight="balanced", # Handle class imbalance[m
[32m+[m[32m    C=2.0,                   # Inverse of regularization strength[m
[32m+[m[32m    random_state=42          # Reproducibility[m
[32m+[m[32m)[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Step 3: Pipeline**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32m# Combine vectorizer + classifier[m
[32m+[m[32mpipeline = Pipeline([[m
[32m+[m[32m    ("tfidf", TfidfVectorizer(...)),[m
[32m+[m[32m    ("clf", LogisticRegression(...))[m
[32m+[m[32m])[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Train[m
[32m+[m[32mpipeline.fit(X_train, y_train)[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
