[32m+[m[32m## 2.4 Model 4: Priority Scorer (Gradient Boosting)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2.4.1 Problem Statement[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Question to Answer:** How urgent is this complaint (0-100 score)?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Why This Matters:**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Need to sort thousands of complaints by urgency[m
[32m+[m[32m- Supervisors need to decide which to handle first[m
[32m+[m[32m- Resource allocation depends on priority[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2.4.2 The Priority Formula (Ground Truth)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBefore training the model, we defined what "priority" means using a human-interpretable formula:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mPriority Score =[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m  Severity (0-36)          ← 12 points per severity level[m
[32m+[m[32m  Sentiment (0-21)        ← 7 points per sentiment level[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m  Amount/5000 (0-20)      ← More money = higher priority[m
[32m+[m[32m  Complaints × 3 (0-12)   ← Repeat customers more urgent[m
[32m+[m[32m  Days old × 0.4 (0-10)   ← Older complaints more urgent[m
[32m+[m[32m  Breach prob × 18 (0-18)← High breach risk = higher priority[m
[32m+[m[32m  Duplicate × -8          ← Duplicates can wait[m
[32m+[m[32m  ─────────────────────────────────────────────[m
[32m+[m[32m  Total: 0-100[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Example Calculations:**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mComplaint A: Critical severity + Angry + Rs.50,000 + First complaint +[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m             1 day old + 80% breach prob[m
[32m+[m[32m           = 36 + 21 + 10 + 0 + 0.4 + 14.4[m
[32m+[m[32m           = 81.4 → Round to 81[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mComplaint B: Low severity + Polite + Rs.1,000 + Repeat customer (3x) +[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m             10 days old + 20% breach prob[m
[32m+[m[32m           = 0 + 0 + 0 + 9 + 4 + 3.6[m
[32m+[m[32m           = 16.6 → Round to 17[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2.4.3 Algorithm: Gradient Boosting Machine (GBM)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**What is Gradient Boosting?**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mLike XGBoost, but WITHOUT the regularization (simpler version). It's a ensemble of decision trees that build sequentially.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**How It's Different from XGBoost:**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Aspect | XGBoost | Gradient Boosting |[m
[32m+[m[32m|--------|---------|-------------------|[m
[32m+[m[32m| Regularization | L1 + L2 | None |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Tree building | Better split finding | Standard |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Speed | Faster | Slower |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Use case | Classification | Regression (our case) |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2.4.4 Why Train a Model If There's a Formula?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Great question!** Why not just use the formula directly?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**The Answer:**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **Missing Data Problem:** The formula needs features we might not have for NEW complaints:[m
[32m+[m[32m   - For a brand new complaint: breach_probability = ? (need to predict it!)[m
[32m+[m[32m   - customer_complaint_count = ? (need to check history)[m
[32m+[m[32m   - days_since_filed = ? (need to compute)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **Learning Real Patterns:** The formula uses FIXED weights (e.g., severity × 12). A trained model can LEARN that for THIS bank, severity matters MORE than the formula assumed.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **Smoothing:** When some features are missing, the model can "interpolate" intelligently, while the formula would break.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m4. **Future Improvement:** Once we have real outcome data (which complaints actually escalated), we can retrain the model to learn BETTER weights than our fixed formula.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2.4.5 Features Used[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Feature | Type | Source |[m
[32m+[m[32m|---------|------|--------|[m
[32m+[m[32m| severity_encoded | Numeric (0-3) | Mapped from severity |[m
[32m+[m[32m| sentiment_encoded | Numeric (0-3) | Mapped from sentiment |[m
[32m+[m[32m| amount_involved | Numeric | Direct from complaint |[m
[32m+[m[32m| customer_complaint_count | Numeric | Count from DB |[m
[32m+[m[32m| days_since_filed | Numeric | Calculated |[m
[32m+[m[32m| is_duplicate | Binary (0-1) | From duplicate detector |[m
[32m+[m[32m| breach_probability | Numeric (0-1) | From SLA model |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2.4.6 Model Training[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**GBM Parameters:**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32mgbm = GradientBoostingRegressor([m
[32m+[m[32m    n_estimators=300,      # 300 trees[m
