[32m+[m[32m## What It Does[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPredicts the probability (0-100%) that a complaint will miss its RBI-mandated SLA deadline.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Why We Need It[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRBI mandates specific response times:[m
[32m+[m[32m- UPI/ATM: 5 days[m
[32m+[m[32m- Card/NetBanking: 7 days[m
[32m+[m[32m- Loan/General: 30 days[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mMissing deadlines = RBI fines + reputation damage. We need to identify AT-RISK complaints BEFORE they breach.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## How It Works (Simple Explanation)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**XGBoost = Extreme Gradient Boosting**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThink of it as a team of decision experts working together:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mQuestion 1: Is the complaint >80% through its SLA window?[m
[32m+[m[32m           ├── YES → HIGH probability[m
[32m+[m[32m           └── NO → Question 2[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mQuestion 2: Is severity Critical?[m
[32m+[m[32m           ├── YES → HIGH probability[m
[32m+[m[32m           └── NO → Question 3[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mQuestion 3: Is customer Angry?[m
[32m+[m[32m           ├── YES → MEDIUM-HIGH probability[m
[32m+[m[32m           └── NO → Check more features...[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mEach "tree" asks questions and gives a score. XGBoost builds 200 trees, each correcting the previous one's mistakes.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Decision Tree Visualization[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32m┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐[m
[32m+[m[32m│                    XGBOOST DECISION TREE - EXAMPLE                              │[m
[32m+[m[32m├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤[m
[32m+[m[32m│                                                                                 │[m
[32m+[m[32m│                         ┌─────────────────────┐                                │[m
