[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Model 3: Sentiment Model (RoBERTa)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## What It Does[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mDetects customer sentiment: **Positive, Neutral, Negative** (then mapped to our 4-class system)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Why We Need It[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Angry customers need URGENT response[m
[32m+[m[32m- Sentiment affects priority scoring[m
[32m+[m[32m- Sentiment affects risk scoring[m
[32m+[m[32m- Sentiment affects auto-resolution (Polite + Low/Medium = auto-resolve)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## How It Works (Simple Explanation)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**What is a Transformer?**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBefore transformers, computers read text word-by-word:[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32m"The" → "customer" → "is" → "angry"[m
[32m+[m[32mHard to remember long context![m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mTransformers read ALL words at once and learn which relate to which:[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32m"The customer is angry" → attention shows "angry" connects to "customer"[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**What is RoBERTa?**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRoBERTa = Robustly Optimized BERT[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Pre-trained on 850 million tweets (!)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Fine-tuned for sentiment analysis[m
[32m+[m[32m- From HuggingFace: `cardiffnlp/twitter-roberta-base-sentiment-latest`[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## How It Works (Technical)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mInput: "UPI payment failed, so angry!!"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mStep 1: Tokenize[m
[32m+[m[32m["UPI", "payment", "failed", ",", "so", "angry", "!!"][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mStep 2: Convert to embeddings[m
[32m+[m[32m[0.12, -0.45, ...] (768 numbers per token)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mStep 3: Pass through 12 Transformer layers[m
[32m+[m[32mEach layer has:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Multi-head self-attention (12 heads)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Feed-forward network[m
[32m+[m[32m- Layer normalization[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mStep 4: Classification[m
[32m+[m[32m768 dimensions → 3 classes[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mOutput:[m
[32m+[m[32m{[m
[32m+[m[32m  "negative": 0.90,[m
[32m+[m[32m  "neutral": 0.08,[m
[32m+[m[32m  "positive": 0.02[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Visual: Why Semantic Similarity Works[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32m┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐[m
[32m+[m[32m│           UNDERSTANDING SEMANTIC EMBEDDINGS                                 │[m
[32m+[m[32m├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤[m
[32m+[m[32m│                                                                             │[m
[32m+[m[32m│  TRADITIONAL KEYWORD MATCHING:                                              │[m
[32m+[m[32m│  ─────────────────────────────────                                          │[m
[32m+[m[32m│  "UPI not working" ✗                                                        │[m
[32m+[m[32m│  "UPI payment failed" ✗  ← Different words = different!                   │[m
[32m+[m[32m│                                                                             │[m
[32m+[m[32m│  SEMANTIC EMBEDDINGS (Our Approach):                                        │[m
[32m+[m[32m│  ─────────────────────────────────                                          │[m
[32m+[m[32m│                                                                             │[m
[32m+[m[32m│  "UPI not working"     ──────────────►  [0.12, -0.45, 0.67, ...]          │[m
[32m+[m[32m│                                       ╲                                     │[m
[32m+[m[32m│                                        ╲  COSINE SIMILARITY = 0.92          │[m
[32m+[m[32m│                                         ╲ (Very similar!)                   │[m
[32m+[m[32m│  "UPI payment failed"  ──────────────►  [0.11, -0.44, 0.68, ...]          │[m
[32m+[m[32m│                                                                             │[m
[32m+[m[32m│  ─────────────────────────────────                                          │[m
[32m+[m[32m│                                                                             │[m
[32m+[m[32m│  "ATM broken"         ──────────────►  [0.89, 0.12, -0.34, ...]           │[m
[32m+[m[32m│                                       ╲                                     │[m
[32m+[m[32m│                                        ╲  COSINE SIMILARITY = 0.15          │[m
[32m+[m[32m│                                         ╲ (Different!)                     │[m
[32m+[m[32m│  "UPI payment failed" ──────────────►  [0.11, -0.44, 0.68, ...]           │[m
[32m+[m[32m│                                                                             │[m
[32m+[m[32m│  KEY INSIGHT: Similar MEANING = Similar embeddings                          │[m
[32m+[m[32m│              Different MEANING = Different embeddings                       │[m
[32m+[m[32m│                                                                             │[m
[32m+[m[32m└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Mapping to Our 4-Class System[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe model outputs 3 classes, but we use 4:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mRoBERTa → Our System:[m
[32m+[m[32mPositive → Polite[m
[32m+[m[32mNeutral  → Neutral[m
[32m+[m[32mNegative → Angry OR Frustrated[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Why 48% Agreement with LLM?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis sounds low but is actually a MAPPING issue:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- RoBERTa: 3 classes (Positive/Neutral/Negative)[m
[32m+[m[32m- LLM: 4 classes (Angry/Frustrated/Neutral/Polite)[m
[32m+[m[32m- "Angry" and "Frustrated" both map to "Negative"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhen LLM says "Frustrated" and RoBERTa says "Negative" → that's a MATCH in our mapping![m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## When & Where Used[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **When:** As second opinion after LLM[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Where:** `agents/sentiment_ml.py` → `predict()`[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Output:** `{label: "negative", score: 0.90, bucket: "negative"}`[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Model 4: Priority Scorer (Gradient Boosting)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## What It Does[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCalculates a priority score (0-100) for sorting complaints by urgency[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Why We Need It[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Not all complaints are equally urgent[m
[32m+[m[32m- Supervisors need to prioritize workload[m
[32m+[m[32m- Need mathematically-grounded sorting[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## The Ground Truth Formula[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBefore training, we defined priority using a human formula:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mPriority =[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m  Severity (0-36)      ← 12 points × severity level (0-3)[m
[32m+[m[32m+ Sentiment (0-21)    ← 7 points × sentiment level (0-3)[m
[32m+[m[32m+ Amount/5000 (0-20)  ← clipped at 20[m
[32m+[m[32m+ Complaints×3 (0-12)  ← customer complaint count × 3, clipped at 12[m
[32m+[m[32m+ Days×0.4 (0-10)     ← days since filed × 0.4, clipped at 10[m
[32m+[m[32m+ Breach×18 (0-18)    ← breach probability × 18[m
[32m+[m[32m- Duplicate×8         ← -8 if duplicate (can wait)[m
[32m+[m[32m───────────────────────────────────────────────[m
[32m+[m[32mTotal: 0-100[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Why Train a Model If Formula Exists?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThree reasons:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **Missing Data:** For NEW complaints, we don't know the outcome. The formula needs `breach_probability` as input - but that's ALSO a prediction![m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **Learning Real Patterns:** The formula uses FIXED weights. Maybe for THIS bank, severity matters MORE than we thought. The model can learn better weights from data.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **Smoothing:** When features are missing, the model interpolates intelligently. Formula would break.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## How It Works[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mUses **Gradient Boosting Machine (GBM)** - similar to XGBoost but without regularization:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32mgbm = GradientBoostingRegressor([m
[32m+[m[32m    n_estimators=300,   # 300 trees[m
[32m+[m[32m    max_depth=4,        # Max 4 levels per tree[m
[32m+[m[32m    learning_rate=0.06,# Shrinkage[m
[32m+[m[32m    subsample=0.9      # Use 90% data per tree[m
[32m+[m[32m)[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mFeatures used:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. severity_encoded (0-3)[m
[32m+[m[32m2. sentiment_encoded (0-3)[m
[32m+[m[32m3. amount_involved[m
[32m+[m[32m4. customer_complaint_count[m
[32m+[m[32m5. days_since_filed[m
[32m+[m[32m6. is_duplicate[m
[32m+[m[32m7. breach_probability[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Results[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **R² Score:** 0.997 (explains 99.7% of variance)[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Mean Absolute Error:** 0.50 (off by only 0.5 points on average)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Feature Importance[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Rank | Feature | Importance |[m
[32m+[m[32m|------|---------|-------------|[m
[32m+[m[32m| 1 | breach_probability | Most important |[m
[32m+[m[32m| 2 | severity_encoded | Second |[m
[32m+[m[32m| 3 | sentiment_encoded | Third |[m
[32m+[m[32m| 4 | amount_involved | Fourth |[m
[32m+[m[32m| 5 | customer_complaint_count | Fifth |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## When & Where Used[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **When:** Every complaint needs sorting[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Where:** `agents/priority.py` → `score()`[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Output:** Priority score 0-100[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
