[32m+[m[32m# Model 5: Duplicate Detector (ChromaDB + Sentence-Transformers)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## What It Does[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mDetects if a complaint is a DUPLICATE - same customer, same issue, different channel[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Why We Need It[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Duplicates waste resources[m
[32m+[m[32m- Duplicate handling differs (auto-resolve without drafting new response)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Different from "systemic issue" (different customers = systemic, same customer = duplicate)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## How It Works (Simple Explanation)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**The Problem:** Traditional duplicate detection uses exact keyword matching:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32m"UPI not working" ≠ "UPI payment failed" (different words, same meaning!)[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Our Solution:** Semantic similarity using embeddings[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32m"UPI not working" → [0.12, -0.45, 0.67, ...] (384 numbers)[m
[32m+[m[32m"UPI payment failed" → [0.11, -0.44, 0.68, ...] (similar!)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mSimilarity = 0.95 (very similar!)[m
[32m+[m[32m→ Flagged as duplicate[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
