[32m+[m[32m# Model 6: Root Cause Detection (KMeans Clustering)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## What It Does[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mDetects SYSTEMIC ISSUES - clusters of similar complaints from multiple customers that indicate a underlying problem[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Why We Need It[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Individual complaints are noise. Systemic issues are signal.**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mExample:[m
[32m+[m[32m- 47 complaints about "UPI failed" from Nagpur over 7 days[m
[32m+[m[32m- No single complaint flags this[m
[32m+[m[32m- But together → clear pattern → fix the gateway![m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis is what Root Cause Agent finds.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## How It Works (Simple Explanation)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**KMeans Clustering Algorithm:**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **Start:** Randomly place 12 centroids (cluster centers) in the 384-dimensional embedding space[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **Assign:** Each complaint goes to its nearest centroid[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **Update:** Move each centroid to the center of its assigned complaints[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m4. **Repeat:** Steps 2-3 until centroids stop moving (convergence)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m5. **Analyze:** Look for clusters that are:[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Large (≥5 complaints)[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Dominated by one category (≥60%)[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Located in same area (≥40% in one city)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## The Math Behind KMeans[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mGoal: Minimize within-cluster variance[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mminimize: Σ ||x_i - μ_{c(i)}||²[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhere:[m
[32m+[m[32m- x_i = embedding of complaint i (384 numbers)[m
[32m+[m[32m- μ_c = centroid of cluster c[m
[32m+[m[32m- c(i) = cluster assignment of complaint i[m
[32m+[m[32m- ||...||² = squared distance[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIn plain English: "Make each cluster as tight as possible around its center"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Input: Embeddings from Duplicate Detector[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe Root Cause Agent REUSES embeddings from the Duplicate Detector:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32m# In root_cause.py[m
[32m+[m[32mfrom agents import duplicate_detector as dd[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mcoll = dd._get_collection()  # Reuse ChromaDB collection![m
[32m+[m[32mres = coll.get(include=["embeddings", "metadatas"])[m
[32m+[m[32membeddings = res["embeddings"]  # 384 dimensions each[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis saves computation - no re-embedding needed.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Systemic Issue Detection Criteria[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mFor each cluster:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **Size Check:** ≥ 5 complaints?[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **Category Dominance:** ≥ 60% same category?[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **Location Analysis:** Top-3 cities by count[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mExamples:[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mCluster 1:[m
[32m+[m[32m- 47 complaints[m
[32m+[m[32m- 95% UPI category → DOMINANT[m
[32m+[m[32m- 80% from Nagpur → one city hotspot[m
[32m+[m[32m→ "47 UPI complaints in Nagpur - possible local service issue"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCluster 2:[m
[32m+[m[32m- 23 complaints[m
[32m+[m[32m- 70% Card category → DOMINANT[m
[32m+[m[32m- 35% Mumbai, 25% Delhi, 20% Bangalore → three cities[m
[32m+[m[32m→ "23 Card complaints across Mumbai, Delhi, Bangalore - possible systemic Card issue"[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Parameters Used[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **k = 12** (number of clusters)[m
[32m+[m[32m- **n_init = 10** (try 10 different initializations)[m
[32m+[m[32m- **random_state = 42** (reproducibility)[m
[32m+[m[32m- **MIN_CLUSTER_SIZE = 5** (minimum for alert)[m
[32m+[m[32m- **DOMINANCE_THRESHOLD = 0.60** (60% category dominance)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Results[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **6 systemic root cause clusters detected**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Examples:[m
[32m+[m[32m  - "47 UPI complaints in Nagpur"[m
[32m+[m[32m  - "38 Card complaints across major cities"[m
[32m+[m[32m  - "25 NetBanking issues in Mumbai"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## When & Where Used[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **When:** Batch analysis after all complaints processed[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Where:** `agents/root_cause.py` → `detect()`[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Output:** List of alerts with cluster_id, category, location, count, summary[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
