[32m+[m[32m# Model 7: Customer Risk Score (Weighted Formula)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## What It Does[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCalculates a risk score (0-100) for each customer based on their complaint history and likelihood of escalation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Why We Need It[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Not all customers are equal risk[m
[32m+[m[32m- Some customers are likely to escalate to RBI Ombudsman[m
[32m+[m[32m- Some might churn (leave the bank)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Some might cause social media backlash[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWe need to identify HIGH-RISK customers for proactive management.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Three Risk Components[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 1. RBI Ombudsman Escalation Risk (45% weight)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhat drives formal RBI complaints:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Breach probability (from SLA model)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Severity (Critical = 30 pts, High = 20, Medium = 10, Low = 3)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Repeat complaints (up to +15 pts)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Amount involved (≥1L = +12 pts, ≥25k = +6 pts)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Angry sentiment history (up to +8 pts)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mombudsman_score = breach_prob×40 + severity_pts + repeat_pts + amount_pts + angry_pts[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2. Churn Risk (30% weight)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhat drives customer leaving:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Total complaints (more = more frustrated)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Unresolved count (unresolved issues = churn risk)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Category breadth (touched many categories = systemic dissatisfaction)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Current sentiment/severity[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mchurn_score = n_complaints×6 + unresolved×5 + categories×6 + sentiment_pts[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 3. Social Media Risk (25% weight)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhat drives public backlash:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Twitter/WhatsApp channel use (public = visibility)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Angry sentiment (angry + public = PR problem)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Critical severity[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32msocial_score = public_channel_complaints×12 + current_channel_risk + angry_pts + critical_pts[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Composite Formula[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mOverall Risk =[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m  0.45 × ombudsman_score +[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m  0.30 × churn_score +[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m  0.25 × social_score[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAll scores clipped to 0-100, final weighted score also 0-100.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Why These Weights?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Ombudsman (45%):** Highest business impact - RBI fines + reputation[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Churn (30%):** Customer retention is crucial[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Social (25%):** Public visibility matters but less than formal escalation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Results[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRisk scores calculated for all 1000 complaints:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Low risk (0-30): ~60% of customers[m
[32m+[m[32m- Medium risk (31-60): ~30% of customers[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- High risk (61-100): ~10% of customers[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## When & Where Used[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **When:** Every complaint processed[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Where:** `agents/risk_score.py` → `compute()`[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Output:** `{ombudsman: 75, churn: 60, social: 45, overall: 62}`[m
[32m+[m
