[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 3.4 Model 4: Priority Scorer (Gradient Boosting) (2 minutes)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m> "Fourth - how do we decide which complaint to handle first?[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **The Problem It Solves:**[m
[32m+[m[32m> With thousands of complaints, how do supervisors prioritize? They need a mathematically-grounded way to sort.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Our Solution: Gradient Boosting**[m
[32m+[m[32m> We use Gradient Boosting Machine (GBM) to create a 0-100 priority score.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **The Ground Truth Formula:**[m
[32m+[m[32m> Before training, we defined what 'priority' means using a human formula:[m
[32m+[m[32m> ```[m
[32m+[m[32m> Priority =[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m>   Severity × 12        (0-36 points)[m
[32m+[m[32m> + Sentiment × 7        (0-21 points)[m
[32m+[m[32m> + Amount / 5000        (0-20, clipped)[m
[32m+[m[32m> + Complaints × 3       (0-12, clipped)[m
[32m+[m[32m> + Days × 0.4          (0-10, clipped)[m
[32m+[m[32m> + Breach probability × 18 (0-18)[m
[32m+[m[32m> - 8 if duplicate      (-8)[m
[32m+[m[32m> ```[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> Example: A Critical (3×12=36) + Angry (3×7=21) + Rs.50,000 (50,000/5000=10) + 80% breach probability (0.8×18=14.4) complaint = 36+21+10+14.4 = 81.4 → Priority 81[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Why Train a Model If Formula Exists?**[m
[32m+[m[32m> Three reasons:[m
[32m+[m[32m> 1. Missing data: For NEW complaints, we don't know the outcome. The formula needs breach_probability as input - but that's also a prediction![m
[32m+[m[32m> 2. Learning: The formula uses FIXED weights. Maybe for our bank, severity matters MORE than we thought. The model learns better weights from data.[m
[32m+[m[32m> 3. Smoothing: When features are missing, the formula breaks. The model interpolates intelligently.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Results:**[m
[32m+[m[32m> - R² Score: 0.997 (explains 99.7% of variance!)[m
[32m+[m[32m> - Mean Absolute Error: Only 0.5 points off on average[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> This gives operations teams a reliable way to sort thousands of complaints by true urgency.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **[Pause for questions]**[m
