[32m+[m[32m## 3.5 Model 5: Duplicate Detector (ChromaDB + Sentence-Transformers) (3 minutes)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m> "Fifth - detecting duplicate complaints.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **The Problem It Solves:**[m
[32m+[m[32m> Same customer, same issue, different channel - this is a duplicate. We need to detect these because they get auto-resolved without drafting a new response (saves 18.6% of workload!). BUT - different customers with the same issue is a SYSTEMIC problem, NOT a duplicate.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Our Solution: Sentence-Transformers + ChromaDB**[m
[32m+[m[32m> We use two technologies working together.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Component 1: Sentence-Transformers**[m
[32m+[m[32m> Model: all-MiniLM-L6-v2[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m> This creates 384-dimensional embeddings - dense vectors that capture SEMANTIC meaning, not just keywords.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> Here's the key insight:[m
[32m+[m[32m> - "UPI not working" and "UPI payment failed" → SIMILAR embeddings (similar meaning!)[m
[32m+[m[32m> - "UPI not working" and "ATM broken" → DIFFERENT embeddings (different meaning!)[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> The model was trained on millions of sentence pairs, learning that similar meanings should have similar vectors.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Component 2: ChromaDB**[m
[32m+[m[32m> ChromaDB is a vector database that stores embeddings and enables fast similarity search.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **The Algorithm:**[m
[32m+[m[32m> 1. Index: Every complaint is embedded and stored in ChromaDB with metadata (customer name, category, location)[m
[32m+[m[32m> 2. Query: For new complaint, embed it[m
[32m+[m[32m> 3. Search: Find top-5 most similar complaints FROM SAME CUSTOMER ONLY[m
[32m+[m[32m> 4. Compare: If cosine similarity ≥ 0.78 → DUPLICATE[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Why Same Customer Only?**[m
[32m+[m[32m> This is critical! If DIFFERENT customers complain about "UPI failed" - that's NOT a duplicate. That's a SYSTEMIC issue (handled by Root Cause Detection). A duplicate is ONLY when the SAME customer raises the same complaint again.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Threshold Selection:**[m
[32m+[m[32m> We tested different thresholds:[m
[32m+[m[32m> - 0.90: Too strict → missed duplicates[m
[32m+[m[32m> - 0.78: Good balance → found 86 duplicates[m
[32m+[m[32m> - 0.70: Too loose → false positives[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> 0.78 was chosen as the sweet spot.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Results:**[m
[32m+[m[32m> - 86 duplicates detected[m
[32m+[m[32m> - 18.6% of complaints auto-resolved (includes duplicates)[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **[Pause for questions]**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 3.6 Model 6: Root Cause Detection (KMeans Clustering) (3 minutes)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m> "Sixth - detecting systemic issues.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **The Problem It Solves:**[m
[32m+[m[32m> Individual complaints are noise. Systemic issues are signal. If 47 customers in Nagpur all complain about UPI in one week - that's ONE problem (gateway failure), not 47 problems. But no human can see this pattern looking at spreadsheets.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Our Solution: KMeans Clustering**[m
[32m+[m[32m> We use unsupervised learning to find clusters of similar complaints.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **How KMeans Works:**[m
[32m+[m[32m> 1. Start: Randomly place 12 centroids in the 384-dimensional embedding space[m
[32m+[m[32m> 2. Assign: Each complaint goes to its nearest centroid[m
[32m+[m[32m> 3. Update: Move each centroid to the center of its assigned complaints[m
[32m+[m[32m> 4. Repeat: Steps 2-3 until centroids stop moving (convergence)[m
[32m+[m[32m> 5. Analyze: Look for clusters that are large (≥5) and dominated by one category (≥60%)[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **The Math:**[m
[32m+[m[32m> KMeans minimizes within-cluster variance:[m
[32m+[m[32m> ```[m
[32m+[m[32m> minimize: Σ ||x_i - μ_c(i)||²[m
[32m+[m[32m> ```[m
[32m+[m[32m> In plain English: Make each cluster as tight as possible around its center.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Reusing Embeddings:**[m
[32m+[m[32m> Importantly, we REUSE the embeddings from the Duplicate Detector - no re-embedding needed. This is efficient![m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Systemic Issue Detection Criteria:**[m
[32m+[m[32m> For each cluster, we check:[m
[32m+[m[32m> 1. Size: At least 5 complaints?[m
[32m+[m[32m> 2. Category Dominance: 60%+ from same category?[m
[32m+[m[32m> 3. Location: Top 3 cities by count[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Example Output:**[m
[32m+[m[32m> ```[m
[32m+[m[32m> Cluster 1:[m
[32m+[m[32m> - 47 complaints[m
[32m+[m[32m> - 95% UPI category → dominant[m
[32m+[m[32m> - 80% from Nagpur → one city hotspot[m
[32m+[m[32m> → ALERT: "47 UPI complaints concentrated in Nagpur - possible local service issue"[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> Cluster 2:[m
[32m+[m[32m> - 38 complaints[m
[32m+[m[32m> - 70% Card category → dominant[m
[32m+[m[32m> - Across Mumbai, Delhi, Bangalore → multiple cities[m
[32m+[m[32m> → ALERT: "38 Card complaints across major cities - possible systemic Card issue"[m
[32m+[m[32m> ```[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **Results:**[m
[32m+[m[32m> - 6 systemic root cause clusters detected[m
[32m+[m[32m> - Examples: "47 UPI in Nagpur", "38 Card across cities", "25 NetBanking in Mumbai"[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> This is something no human can see in spreadsheets - but with KMeans on embeddings, the pattern emerges automatically.[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m
[32m+[m[32m> **[Pause for questions]**[m
[32m+[m
