[32m+[m[32m# 5. Deep Dive: Each Agent Explained[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Agent 1: Intake Agent[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Technology**: Groq LLaMA 3.3 70B (versatile)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Purpose**: Transform raw, messy complaint text into structured data[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**What it does**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Receives: `{"complaint_text": "मेरा UPI काम नहीं कर रहा है, पैसे अटक गए।", "channel": "whatsapp"}`[m
[32m+[m[32m- Returns:[m
[32m+[m[32m  ```json[m
[32m+[m[32m  {[m
[32m+[m[32m    "customer_name": null,[m
[32m+[m[32m    "issue_summary": "UPI payment stuck, funds not credited",[m
[32m+[m[32m    "account_type": "savings",[m
[32m+[m[32m    "amount_involved": null,[m
[32m+[m[32m    "transaction_id": null,[m
[32m+[m[32m    "location_mentioned": null,[m
[32m+[m[32m    "urgency_keywords": ["stuck", "not working"],[m
[32m+[m[32m    "detected_language": "mixed"[m
[32m+[m[32m  }[m
[32m+[m[32m  ```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Why LLM?**: Handles code-mixed Hindi-English, extracts implicit information, summarizes long complaints[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Fallback**: If LLM fails, keyword-based extraction still works[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Agent 2: Classifier Agent[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Technology**: Groq LLaMA 3.3 70B + TF-IDF + Logistic Regression (second opinion)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Purpose**: Assign category, severity, and sentiment[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Category Options**: UPI, ATM, Card, Loan, NetBanking, General[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Severity Definitions**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Critical**: fraud, unauthorized debit, locked out, ≥₹50,000[m
[32m+[m[32m- **High**: amount stuck, repeated failures, account access issues[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Medium**: typical service issues, single failed transaction[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Low**: information requests, minor inconvenience[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Sentiment Options**: Angry, Frustrated, Neutral, Polite[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Output Example**:[m
[32m+[m[32m```json[m
[32m+[m[32m{[m
[32m+[m[32m  "category": "UPI",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "severity": "High",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "sentiment": "Frustrated",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "rationale": "Customer reported stuck UPI transaction with amount details"[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**ML Second Opinion**: TF-IDF + Logistic Regression validates LLM classification (97% accuracy, 98% agreement with LLM)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Agent 3: Duplicate Detector[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Technology**: sentence-transformers (all-MiniLM-L6-v2) + ChromaDB vector database[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Purpose**: Find if same customer already complained about same issue[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**How it works**:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Embed complaint text into 384-dimensional vector using sentence-transformers[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Store in ChromaDB with metadata (customer_name, channel, date, category, location)[m
[32m+[m[32m3. For new complaint, query ONLY same-customer complaints[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Calculate cosine similarity between embeddings[m
[32m+[m[32m5. If similarity ≥ 0.78 → marked as duplicate[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Why same customer only**: Two different customers reporting "UPI failed" is NOT a duplicate—it's a systemic issue (handled by Agent 6)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Results in our dataset**: 86 duplicates detected out of 1000 complaints[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Agent 4: Response Drafter[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Technology**: Groq LLaMA 3.3 70B[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Purpose**: Generate policy-compliant bank reply in customer's language[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Features**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Writes in English, Hindi, or Marathi based on `detected_language`[m
[32m+[m[32m- References complaint details (category, amount, transaction ID)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Provides empathetic acknowledgment[m
[32m+[m[32m- Explains next steps[m
[32m+[m[32m- Includes SLA commitment[m
[32m+[m[32m- Uses professional banking tone[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Example Output (Hindi)**:[m
[32m+[m[32m> "प्रिय ग्राहक जी,[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m> आपके UPI भुगतान संबंधी शिकायत के लिए हमें खेद है। हमने आपकी शिकायत दर्ज कर ली है (ID: UBI-0042)।[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m> हमारी टीम इस मामले की जांच कर रही है और 5 कार्य दिवसों के भीतर आपको अपडेट देगी।[m
[32m+[m[32m>[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m> धन्यवाद,[m
[32m+[m[32m> ग्राहक सेवा विभाग"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Auto-skip**: If duplicate detected, skips drafting (prior complaint already has response)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Agent 5: SLA Monitor[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Technology**: XGBoost (tuned) + rule-based fallback[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Purpose**: Calculate due date + predict breach probability[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**RBI SLA Rules** (from `data/sla_rules.json`):[m
[32m+[m[32m| Category | Base SLA |[m
[32m+[m[32m|----------|----------|[m
[32m+[m[32m| UPI / ATM | 5 days |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Card / NetBanking | 7 days |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Loan / General | 30 days |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Severity Multipliers**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Critical: 0.5× (tightest window)[m
[32m+[m[32m- High: 0.7×[m
[32m+[m[32m- Medium: 1.0×[m
[32m+[m[32m- Low: 1.2× (relaxed window)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**ML Model**: After comparing RF, GBM, XGBoost (tuned), LightGBM, and Stacking ensemble with 5-fold Stratified CV + SMOTE:[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Best Model**: XGBoost (tuned)[m
[32m+[m[32m- **CV AUC**: 0.9233 ± 0.018[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Hold-out AUC**: 0.9378[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Features used**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Channel, language, account type, category, severity, sentiment[m
[32m+[m[32m- Amount involved, text length, word count[m
[32m+[m[32m- Hours since filed, day of week, weekend flag[m
[32m+[m[32m- Fraud keywords, duplicate flag, repeat customer[m
[32m+[m[32m- Days to SLA, % SLA elapsed[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Agent 6: Root Cause Detector[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Technology**: KMeans clustering on sentence embeddings[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Purpose**: Detect SYSTEMIC issues that no single complaint reveals[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Algorithm**:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Collect all complaint embeddings from ChromaDB[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Run KMeans with k=12 clusters[m
[32m+[m[32m3. For each cluster ≥ 5 complaints:[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Check if ≥ 60% share same category[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Check location distribution[m
[32m+[m[32m   - Extract top-3 city hotspots[m
[32m+[m[32m4. If category dominance ≥ 60% → flag as systemic issue[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Example Output**:[m
[32m+[m[32m```json[m
[32m+[m[32m{[m
[32m+[m[32m  "cluster_id": 3,[m
[32m+[m[32m  "category": "UPI",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "location": "Nagpur",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "top_cities": [("Nagpur", 47), ("Mumbai", 12), ("Pune", 8)],[m
[32m+[m[32m  "count": 67,[m
[32m+[m[32m  "category_share": 0.72,[m
[32m+[m[32m  "location_share": 0.58,[m
[32m+[m[32m  "summary": "67 UPI complaints concentrated in Nagpur (58% of cluster) - possible local UPI service issue"[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Why this matters**: Banks can proactively fix gateway issues BEFORE they become RBI problems[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Additional Module: Customer Risk Score[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Purpose**: Composite 0-100 score predicting customer behavior risk[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Formula**:[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mOverall = 0.45 × Ombudsman + 0.30 × Churn + 0.25 × Social[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Ombudsman Sub-score** (45% weight):[m
[32m+[m[32m- Breach probability × 40[m
[32m+[m[32m- Severity bonus (Critical: +30, High: +20, Medium: +10, Low: +3)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Repeat complainer bonus (+3 per complaint, max 15)[m
[32m+[m[32m- High amount bonus (≥₹100k: +12, ≥₹25k: +6)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Angry history bonus (+2 per angry complaint, max 8)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Churn Sub-score** (30% weight):[m
[32m+[m[32m- Total complaints × 6 (max 30)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Unresolved complaints × 5 (max 25)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Categories touched × 6 (max 20)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Angry/Frustrated sentiment +12[m
[32m+[m[32m- Critical/High severity +8[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Social Media Risk Sub-score** (25% weight):[m
[32m+[m[32m- Twitter/WhatsApp complaints × 12 (max 45)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Current complaint on public channel +18[m
[32m+[m[32m- Angry sentiment +22[m
[32m+[m[32m- Frustrated sentiment +10[m
[32m+[m[32m- Critical severity +8[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Result**: 0-100 score with explainable breakdown, stored on each complaint[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# 6. ML Models: The Mathematical Intuition[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 6.1 SLA Breach Predictor (XGBoost)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Problem**: Predict probability that a complaint will miss its RBI SLA deadline[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Algorithm**: XGBoost (Extreme Gradient Boosting)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Why XGBoost?**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Handles mixed categorical + numeric features[m
[32m+[m[32m- Built-in regularization prevents overfitting[m
[32m+[m[32m- Fast inference for real-time prediction[m
[32m+[m[32m- Outperformed RF, GBM, LightGBM, and Stacking in our bake-off[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Mathematical intuition**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Decision trees split on feature values (e.g., "if hours_since_filed > 72")[m
[32m+[m[32m- Gradient boosting minimizes loss function: L = -[y log(ŷ) + (1-y) log(1-ŷ)][m
[32m+[m[32m- XGBoost adds L1/L2 regularization on leaf weights[m
[32m+[m[32m- Final prediction: sigmoid of sum of tree outputs[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Training details**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- 5-fold Stratified Cross-Validation[m
[32m+[m[32m- SMOTE for class imbalance (breach vs. non-breach)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Hyperparameter tuning via grid search[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Results**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- CV AUC: 0.9233 ± 0.018[m
[32m+[m[32m- Hold-out AUC: 0.9378[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 6.2 Category Classifier (TF-IDF + Logistic Regression)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Problem**: Classify complaint into one of 6 categories[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Algorithm**: TF-IDF vectorization → Logistic Regression[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Why this works**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- TF-IDF captures term importance: TF(t,d) × IDF(t)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Logistic Regression outputs probabilities via softmax[m
[32m+[m[32m- Fast, interpretable, works well with short text[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Mathematical intuition**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- TF-IDF: `weight(t,d) = (1 + log(TF(t,d))) × log(N/DF(t))`[m
[32m+[m[32m- Logistic Regression: `P(c|x) = exp(w_c · x) / Σ exp(w_j · x)`[m
[32m+[m[32m- Trained with cross-entropy loss[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Results**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Accuracy: 97%[m
[32m+[m[32m- LLM agreement: 98%[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 6.3 Sentiment Model (RoBERTa)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Problem**: Detect sentiment (positive/neutral/negative) from complaint text[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Algorithm**: cardiffnlp/twitter-roberta-base-sentiment-latest[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Why RoBERTa?**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Pre-trained on 850M tweets[m
[32m+[m[32m- Fine-tuned for sentiment analysis[m
[32m+[m[32m- Local inference (no API calls)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**How it works**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Input: complaint text tokenized via RoBERTa tokenizer[m
[32m+[m[32m- Model: 12-layer transformer with attention[m
[32m+[m[32m- Output: 3-class probability distribution[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Results**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Agreement with LLM: 48% (3-class vs 4-class mismatch)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Used as second opinion, not primary[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 6.4 Priority Scorer (Gradient Boosting)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Problem**: Score complaint priority (0-100) for sorting[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Algorithm**: Gradient Boosting Machine (GBM)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Why GBM?**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Handles non-linear feature interactions[m
[32m+[m[32m- Produces continuous priority scores[m
[32m+[m[32m- Fast training and inference[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Results**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- R²: 0.997[m
[32m+[m[32m- MAE: 0.50[m
