[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# 7. The Vector Database: ChromaDB Explained[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 7.1 What is ChromaDB?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mChromaDB is an open-source embedding database designed for AI applications. It stores, indexes, and searches over vector embeddings—the numerical representations of text that capture semantic meaning.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 7.2 Why ChromaDB for Duplicate Detection?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Traditional approach**: Exact keyword matching[m
[32m+[m[32m- Fails: "UPI not working" ≠ "UPI payment failed" (different words, same meaning)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Our approach**: Semantic similarity via embeddings[m
[32m+[m[32m- "UPI not working" and "UPI payment failed" → similar vectors → detected as duplicates[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 7.3 Technical Implementation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Embedding Model**: `sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2`[m
[32m+[m[32m- 384-dimensional embeddings[m
[32m+[m[32m- Cosine similarity space[m
[32m+[m[32m- Fast (CPU inference < 50ms)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Storage**:[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32m# Persistent storage in data/chroma_db/[m
[32m+[m[32mchroma_client = chromadb.PersistentClient(path="./data/chroma_db")[m
[32m+[m[32mcollection = chroma_client.get_or_create_collection([m
[32m+[m[32m    name="complaints",[m
[32m+[m[32m    metadata={"hnsw:space": "cosine"}[m
[32m+[m[32m)[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Indexing**:[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32mcollection.upsert([m
[32m+[m[32m    ids=[complaint_id],[m
[32m+[m[32m    embeddings=[embedding_vector],[m
[32m+[m[32m    documents=[complaint_text],[m
[32m+[m[32m    metadatas=[{[m
[32m+[m[32m        "customer_name": "...",[m
[32m+[m[32m        "channel": "...",[m
[32m+[m[32m        "date": "...",[m
[32m+[m[32m        "category": "...",[m
[32m+[m[32m        "location": "..."[m
[32m+[m[32m    }][m
[32m+[m[32m)[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Querying** (for duplicate detection):[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32mresults = collection.query([m
[32m+[m[32m    query_embeddings=[query_embedding],[m
[32m+[m[32m    n_results=5,[m
[32m+[m[32m    where={"customer_name": "Same Customer"}[m
[32m+[m[32m)[m
[32m+[m[32m# Returns: IDs, distances (1 - cosine similarity), metadata[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Threshold**: 0.78 cosine similarity → duplicate flag[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 7.4 Persistence[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- ChromaDB persists to disk[m
[32m+[m[32m- Survives restarts[m
[32m+[m[32m- Ships with repo (in `data/chroma_db/`)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# 8. Root Cause Detection: KMeans Clustering Deep Dive[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 8.1 The Problem We're Solving[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIndividual complaints are noise. Systemic issues are signal.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mExample:[m
[32m+[m[32m- 47 complaints: "UPI failed" from Nagpur over 7 days[m
[32m+[m[32m- No single complaint flags this[m
[32m+[m[32m- But together → clear pattern → fix the gateway[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 8.2 KMeans Algorithm[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Input**: Set of 384-dimensional embeddings (one per complaint)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Parameters**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- k = 12 clusters (chosen empirically)[m
[32m+[m[32m- n_init = 10 (different centroid seeds)[m
[32m+[m[32m- random_state = 42 (reproducibility)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Algorithm**:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Initialize k centroids randomly[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Assign each point to nearest centroid[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Recalculate centroids as mean of assigned points[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Repeat 2-3 until convergence (max 300 iterations)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Mathematical formulation**:[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mminimize: Σ ||x_i - μ_{c(i)}||²[m
[32m+[m[32mwhere:[m
[32m+[m[32m  x_i = embedding of complaint i[m
[32m+[m[32m  μ_c = centroid of cluster c[m
[32m+[m[32m  c(i) = cluster assignment of complaint i[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 8.3 Systemic Issue Detection[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAfter clustering, for each cluster:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **Check minimum size**: ≥ 5 complaints[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **Check category dominance**: ≥ 60% same category[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **Analyze location**: Extract top-3 cities[m
[32m+[m[32m4. **Generate alert**: If criteria met[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Example**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Cluster 3: 67 complaints[m
[32m+[m[32m- 72% are "UPI" category[m
[32m+[m[32m- 58% are from "Nagpur"[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Alert**: "67 UPI complaints concentrated in Nagpur - possible local UPI service issue"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 8.4 Results[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- 6 root cause clusters detected[m
[32m+[m[32m- Each with category, location, count, top-cities, summary[m
[32m+[m[32m- Stored in `root_cause_alerts` table[m
[32m+[m[32m- Displayed on dashboard "Root Cause" tab[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# 9. Risk Score: The Weighted Formula Explained[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 9.1 Why Risk Scoring?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mNot all customers are equal risk. Some will escalate to RBI Ombudsman. Some will close their accounts. Some will blast the bank on Twitter. We score each to prioritize attention.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 9.2 The Composite Score Formula[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mOverall Risk Score (0-100) =[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m  0.45 × Ombudsman Score[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m+ 0.30 × Churn Score[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m+ 0.25 × Social Media Score[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Weights chosen based on**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Ombudsman (45%)**: Highest impact—RBI fines, regulatory scrutiny[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Churn (30%)**: Second highest—customer retention value[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Social (25%)**: Reputation risk, but harder to predict[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 9.3 Sub-Score Calculations[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Ombudsman Escalation Score[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32mscore = breach_probability * 40          # ML prediction weight[m
[32m+[m[32mscore += {"Critical": 30, "High": 20, "Medium": 10, "Low": 3}[severity][m
[32m+[m[32mscore += min(complaint_count * 3, 15)    # Repeat complainer[m
[32m+[m[32mscore += {">=100k": 12, ">=25k": 6, "<25k": 0}[amount_tier][m
[32m+[m[32mscore += min(angry_history_count * 2, 8)[m
[32m+[m[32mscore = clip(score, 0, 100)[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Churn Risk Score[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32mscore = min(complaint_count * 6, 30)[m
[32m+[m[32mscore += min(unresolved_count * 5, 25)[m
[32m+[m[32mscore += min(category_breadth * 6, 20)   # Multiple categories = systemic dissatisfaction[m
[32m+[m[32mscore += (sentiment in ["Angry", "Frustrated"]) * 12[m
[32m+[m[32mscore += (severity in ["Critical", "High"]) * 8[m
[32m+[m[32mscore = clip(score, 0, 100)[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Social Media Blow-up Score[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32mscore = min(twitter_whatsapp_count * 12, 45)[m
[32m+[m[32mscore += (current_channel in ["twitter", "whatsapp"]) * 18[m
[32m+[m[32mscore += {"Angry": 22, "Frustrated": 10, "Neutral": 0, "Polite": 0}[sentiment][m
[32m+[m[32mscore += (severity == "Critical") * 8[m
[32m+[m[32mscore = clip(score, 0, 100)[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 9.4 Explainability[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mEvery score is broken into sub-components. The dashboard shows:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Overall gauge (0-100)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Three sub-score bars (Ombudsman / Churn / Social)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Explanation of contributing factors[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
