[32m+[m[32m# 16. Q&A Preparation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Q1: How does ComplaintIQ handle multi-language complaints?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**A**: We use Groq LLaMA 3.3 which has excellent multilingual capabilities. The Intake Agent detects language (English/Hindi/Marathi/mixed) and the Response Drafter writes replies in the customer's detected language. Our training data includes all three languages.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Q2: What happens if the LLM API is unavailable?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**A**: Every agent has a deterministic fallback:[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Intake**: Keyword-based extraction returns minimal fields[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Classifier**: Regex patterns for category, severity heuristics[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Response Drafter**: Returns "Please contact support" template[m
[32m+[m[32m- **SLA Monitor**: Rule-based probability calculation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe pipeline NEVER fails—always returns a result.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Q3: How do you handle data privacy?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**A**:[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m- All data stored locally in SQLite (no external cloud)[m
[32m+[m[32m- ChromaDB persists locally in `data/chroma_db/`[m
[32m+[m[32m- No PII sent to external APIs beyond Groq (which is processed in their cloud)[m
[32m+[m[32m- For production: would use on-premise LLM or private deployment[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Q4: How does the root cause detection work mathematically?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**A**: We use KMeans clustering on 384-dimensional sentence embeddings. Each cluster represents complaints with similar semantic meaning. We flag clusters where ≥60% share the same category AND have ≥5 complaints—this catches systemic issues like "47 UPI failures in Nagpur."[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Q5: Can this scale to millions of complaints?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**A**: Current architecture:[m
[32m+[m[32m- SQLite: Good for <100k rows[m
[32m+[m[32m- For millions: Migrate to PostgreSQL[m
[32m+[m[32m- ChromaDB: Can add more instances or use client-side sharding[m
[32m+[m[32m- LLM API: Would need Groq enterprise or self-hosted LLaMA[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Design is modular**: swap SQLite→PostgreSQL, swap Groq→self-hosted, keep rest of pipeline unchanged.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Q6: How do you calculate the customer risk score?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**A**: It's a weighted composite:[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Ombudsman (45%)**: Based on breach probability, severity, amount, repeat complaints[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Churn (30%)**: Based on complaint count, unresolved issues, category breadth[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Social (25%)**: Based on Twitter/WhatsApp usage, angry sentiment[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAll three are calculated from complaint metadata and history. Formula is transparent and stored in `agents/risk_score.py`.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Q7: What if the ML model disagrees with the LLM?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**A**: We show a `(*)` marker on the dashboard when ML and LLM disagree. The dashboard displays both values:[m
[32m+[m[32m- LLM classification (primary)[m
[32m+[m[32m- ML classification (second opinion)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Agreement rate: 98% for category, 48% for sentiment (different class systems)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Q8: How do auto-resolution rules work?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**A**: Two rules:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **Duplicate**: If Agent 3 detects duplicate, mark `auto_resolved_dup`[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **Standard reply**: If severity ∈ {Low, Medium} AND sentiment = Polite AND category has template, mark `auto_resolved_std`[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis cleared 186/1000 (18.6%) of workload automatically.[m
[32m+[m
