[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Q11: What's the deployment story?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**A**:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Streamlit Cloud (free): Works out of the box with pre-seeded SQLite and trained models[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Local: `streamlit run dashboard/app.py`[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Production: Dockerize, use PostgreSQL, self-hosted LLM[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Q12: How do you handle duplicate complaints?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**A**:[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m- Embed complaint text with sentence-transformers[m
[32m+[m[32m- Store in ChromaDB indexed by customer_name[m
[32m+[m[32m- Query only same-customer complaints[m
[32m+[m[32m- Cosine similarity ≥ 0.78 → duplicate[m
[32m+[m[32m- Auto-resolve duplicates without drafting new response[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Q13: What's the technology behind sentiment analysis?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**A**: We use `cardiffnlp/twitter-roberta-base-sentiment-latest`:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Pre-trained on 850M tweets[m
[32m+[m[32m- Fine-tuned for sentiment[m
[32m+[m[32m- Runs locally (no API calls)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Outputs: positive/neutral/negative with confidence scores[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Q14: How does the feedback loop work?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**A**:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. User clicks "Correct" or "Wrong" on dashboard[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Records to `feedback` table in SQLite[m
[32m+[m[32m3. If wrong, corrected value updates the complaint row[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Feedback stats displayed on "Feedback" tab[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Q15: Why 6 agents? Why not fewer or more?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**A**:[m
[32m+[m[32m- **1 (Intake)**: Structural extraction—different from classification[m
[32m+[m[32m- **2 (Classifier)**: Category/severity/sentiment—semantic understanding[m
[32m+[m[32m- **3 (Duplicate)**: Vector similarity—needs separate agent[m
[32m+[m[32m- **4 (Response)**: Generative—needs LLM[m
[32m+[m[32m- **5 (SLA)**: Predictive ML—different paradigm[m
[32m+[m[32m- **6 (Root Cause)**: Clustering—batch, not per-complaint[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mMore agents = more modularity, easier to swap one component without breaking others.[m
