[32m+[m[32m## 5. ML Models: The Mathematical Intuition[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Model 1: SLA Breach Predictor (XGBoost)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### What is XGBoost?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**XGBoost = eXtreme Gradient Boosting**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThink of it like building a team of decision makers:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mIndividual decision trees:[m
[32m+[m[32m├── Tree 1: "If severity=Critical AND breach_prob > 0.5 → High risk"[m
[32m+[m[32m├── Tree 2: "If amount > 25000 AND is_repeat_customer → High risk"[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m└── Tree 3: "If channel=twitter AND sentiment=Angry → High risk"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mXGBoost combines all trees, weighted by their accuracy[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### Gradient Boosting Intuition[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32m# Simplified concept of gradient boosting[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Start with a simple prediction (mean)[m
[32m+[m[32mprediction = 0.18  # 18% base breach rate[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Calculate error for each sample[m
[32m+[m[32merrors = actual_breach - prediction  # [-0.18, 0.82, -0.18, ...][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Train next tree to predict these errors[m
[32m+[m[32mtree2 = train_tree(features, errors)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Update prediction[m
[32m+[m[32mprediction = prediction + learning_rate * tree2.predict(features)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Repeat this 400 times (n_estimators=400)[m
[32m+[m[32m# Final prediction = sum of all trees[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### Feature Importance (What Matters Most)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mFrom the trained model, the top features are:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
