[32m+[m[32m### Model 2: Category Classifier (TF-IDF + Logistic Regression)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### What is TF-IDF?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**TF-IDF = Term Frequency - Inverse Document Frequency**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mMeasures how important a word is to a document in a collection:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mTF-IDF(word, document, corpus) =[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m    TF(word, document) × IDF(word, corpus)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhere:[m
[32m+[m[32m- TF(word, document) = count of word in document / total words[m
[32m+[m[32m- IDF(word, corpus) = log(total documents / documents containing word)[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Example:**[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mDocuments:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. "UPI payment failed"[m
[32m+[m[32m2. "UPI not working"[m
[32m+[m[32m3. "ATM cash not dispensed"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWord "UPI":[m
[32m+[m[32m- TF in doc1: 1/3 = 0.33[m
[32m+[m[32m- IDF: log(3/2) = 0.405[m
[32m+[m[32m- TF-IDF: 0.33 × 0.405 = 0.134[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWord "payment":[m
[32m+[m[32m- TF in doc1: 1/3 = 0.33[m
[32m+[m[32m- IDF: log(3/1) = 1.099[m
[32m+[m[32m- TF-IDF: 0.33 × 1.099 = 0.363[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**So "payment" is more distinctive than "UPI" for categorization!**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### TF-IDF Process[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32m# Input: complaint text[m
[32m+[m[32mtext = "UPI payment failed, amount got debited"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# TF-IDF vectorization[m
[32m+[m[32mvectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=5000)[m
[32m+[m[32mX = vectorizer.fit_transform([text])[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Result: sparse matrix of shape (1, 5000)[m
[32m+[m[32m# Non-zero values at indices corresponding to words[m
[32m+[m[32m# [[m
[32m+[m[32m#     0,    # "atm" = 0[m
[32m+[m[32m#     0,    # "card" = 0[m
[32m+[m[32m#     0.234, # "failed" = 0.234[m
[32m+[m[32m#     0.156, # "payment" = 0.156[m
[32m+[m[32m#     0.412, # "upi" = 0.412[m
[32m+[m[32m#     ...[m
[32m+[m[32m# ][m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### What is Logistic Regression?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mDespite the name, it's a **classifier** (not regression):[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32m# Binary logistic regression[m
[32m+[m[32m# P(breach=1) = 1 / (1 + e^-(b0 + b1*x1 + b2*x2 + ...))[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# For multiclass (6 categories), we train 6 binary classifiers[m
[32m+[m[32m# or use softmax activation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Example: Category prediction[m
[32m+[m[32mlogistic = LogisticRegression()[m
[32m+[m[32mlogistic.fit(X_train, y_train)  # Learn weights[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Predict[m
[32m+[m[32mprediction = logistic.predict(X_new)  # "UPI"[m
[32m+[m[32mprobabilities = logistic.predict_proba(X_new)  # [0.01, 0.94, 0.02, 0.01, 0.01, 0.01][m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### Why This Works[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mTF-IDF + Logistic Regression is a classic combination because:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. TF-IDF converts text → meaningful numbers[m
[32m+[m[32m2. LogReg learns boundaries between categories[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Fast to train and predict[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Interpretable (which words matter for which category)[m
[32m+[m[32m5. Works well with clear categories (UPI vs ATM vs Card)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCategory-specific words:[m
[32m+[m[32m- UPI: "upi", "payment", "transfer", "failed"[m
[32m+[m[32m- ATM: "atm", "cash", "machine", "dispense"[m
[32m+[m[32m- Card: "card", "credit", "debit", "blocked"[m
