[32m+[m[32m## 11. Why Each Choice Over Alternatives[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### LLM: Groq vs OpenAI vs Local Models[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Factor | Groq (Llama 3.3) | OpenAI (GPT-4) | Local (Llama 3 70B) |[m
[32m+[m[32m|--------|------------------|----------------|---------------------|[m
[32m+[m[32m| Speed | ⚡ Very fast | 🐢 Slow | 🐢 Very slow |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Cost | 🆓 Free tier | 💰 Expensive | ⚠️ Hardware cost |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Quality | ✅ Good | ✅ Best | ✅ Good |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Setup | ✅ Easy | ✅ Easy | ❌ Complex |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Latency | ~500ms | ~3000ms | ~30000ms |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Decision: Groq**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Best speed/cost for classification tasks[m
[32m+[m[32m- Good enough quality for structured output[m
[32m+[m[32m- Free tier sufficient for demo/project[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Vector Store: ChromaDB vs Pinecone vs Weaviate[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Factor | ChromaDB | Pinecone | Weaviate |[m
[32m+[m[32m|--------|----------|----------|----------|[m
[32m+[m[32m| Deployment | Local | Cloud | Local/Docker |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Cost | 🆓 Free | 💰 Paid | 🆓 Free |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Filtering | ✅ Easy | ✅ Easy | ✅ |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Persistence | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Setup | 5 min | 10 min | 30 min |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Decision: ChromaDB**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Free, local, persistent[m
[32m+[m[32m- Easy metadata filtering[m
[32m+[m[32m- Simple Python API[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### ML Models: Classical vs Deep Learning[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Factor | Classical (XGB, LogReg) | Deep Learning (BERT, etc.) |[m
[32m+[m[32m|--------|-------------------------|---------------------------|[m
[32m+[m[32m| Data needed | 1,000s | 100,000s |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Training time | Minutes | Hours/Days |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Inference speed | Fast (ms) | Slow (seconds) |[m
[32m+[m[32m| GPU required | Optional | Required |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Interpretability | ✅ Feature importance | ❌ Black box |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Accuracy | ✅ Good enough | ✅ Slightly better |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Decision: Classical ML**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Data size (1000) is enough for classical ML[m
[32m+[m[32m- Interpretable (understand why prediction made)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Fast inference[m
[32m+[m[32m- No GPU required[m
[32m+[m[32m- Good enough accuracy (94% AUC)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Dashboard: Streamlit vs Dash vs React[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Factor | Streamlit | Dash | React + Flask |[m
[32m+[m[32m|--------|-----------|------|---------------|[m
[32m+[m[32m| Development speed | ⚡ Fast | 😐 Medium | ❌ Slow |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Python-only | ✅ | ⚠️ Partial | ❌ Need JS |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Customization | Limited | Good | Unlimited |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Learning curve | Low | Medium | High |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Decision: Streamlit**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Fastest development[m
[32m+[m[32m- Native data science integration[m
[32m+[m[32m- Good enough for internal tool[m
